title: Appointments to SLFAC announced
content_text: The Government today (October 13) gazetted the appointment of a new member and the re-appointment of six members to the Subventions and Lotteries Fund Advisory Committee (SLFAC) for a period of one year with effect from October 1, 2000. The newly appointed member is Mr Albert Lam Chi-chiu. The re-appointed members are Dr Leung Man-fuk, Miss Nancy Tsang, Mr Wong

Che-ming, Mr Vincent Lo Wing-sang, Dr Angelina Yuen Tsang Woon-ki and Mr Tung Chi-fat.  Mr Albert Lam Chi-chiu is the Chief 
    Executive of the Community Chest of Hong Kong. He will provide an important linkage 
    between SLFAC and the Chest. A Government spokesman said, "The 
    members draw together experience from front-line social workers, professionals with 
    building and architectural expertise, as well as members of the public with extensive 
    community service." Together with the other three incumbent
